    title: "Black-Scholes Call With Closed-Form Inputs",
    body: "Price a European call with $S_0 = 100$, $K = 100$, $r = 5\\%$, volatility $\\sigma = 20\\%$, and maturity $T = 1$ year using the Black-Scholes formula. Use $N(0.35) = 0.6368$ and $N(0.15) = 0.5596$.",
